    "Vendor restock arity fix (build 325). Build-324 120-seed grid surfaced a TypeError in 1/120 runs (s=167 dwarf): `generate_vendor_inventory() missing 1 required positional argument: 'room'` at items.py:2391. The function signature at items.py:2403 is `(floor_level, room)` and uses `room.properties.get('restocked', 0)` to scale a restock-penalty markup, but the call site in `restock_vendor_at` was dropping the kwarg. Fixed by passing `vendor_room` (already on hand from the room-type check two lines up). Non-fatal in the harness but a real game-side crash for the rare 'Scroll of Commerce + multi-vendor floor' path. Smoke: s=167 dwarf now reaches F5 (T1345 combat death) without traceback.",
