    "Revert U-camp escape (build 323). Build-322's stairs_up_cancels_this_floor counter + force-ascent branch verified DEAD CODE: across 50 runs, cancels_max==3 reached in 31 runs but forced_ascents==0 in every single run -- the existing retreat-target branch always satisfied first. Tile-cycle bug improved 15/50 -> 9/50 (likely measurement noise from obs-dict key drift), but new pathology emerged: floor-bouncing. s512_human had 104 descents + 103 ascents across F1-F2; net survival regressed (11 -> 9 @ t1500, starvation 24 -> 27). The cancel-escape doesn't address the real failure mode (region-split floors where D is genuinely unreachable AND warp jumps trigger perpetual retreat). Reverted cleanly. The build-321 sealed-pocket gen fix + blacksmith afford-gate remain; both shipped real improvements. Next floor-bounce work will need a retreat-counter / bank-current-floor mechanism, not a U-camp-specific fix.",
